# EcoWare Tech Stack & Dependencies

This document outlines the complete technology stack used in the EcoWare application, including versions and purposes.

## Core Framework & Runtime

### Next.js 15.5.0
- **Purpose**: React framework for full-stack web applications
- **Features**: App Router, Server Components, API routes, built-in optimizations
- **Scripts**: 
  - `dev`: Development server with Turbopack
  - `build`: Production build with Turbopack
  - `start`: Production server

### React 19.1.0 & React DOM 19.1.0
- **Purpose**: UI library and DOM renderer
- **Features**: Latest React features including Concurrent Features, Server Components compatibility
- **Note**: Using the latest stable React 19 release

## Development Environment

### TypeScript ^5
- **Purpose**: Static type checking and enhanced developer experience
- **Version**: Latest TypeScript 5.x series
- **Benefits**: Type safety, better IDE support, improved code quality

### Node.js Types (@types/node ^20)
- **Purpose**: TypeScript definitions for Node.js APIs
- **Version**: Node.js 20 LTS compatible types

### React Types (@types/react ^19, @types/react-dom ^19)
- **Purpose**: TypeScript definitions for React and React DOM
- **Version**: Matching React 19 types

## Styling & UI

### Tailwind CSS ^4
- **Purpose**: Utility-first CSS framework
- **Version**: Latest Tailwind CSS 4.x (next-generation architecture)
- **PostCSS**: Uses @tailwindcss/postcss ^4 for processing

## Code Quality & Linting

### ESLint ^9
- **Purpose**: JavaScript/TypeScript linting and code quality
- **Config**: Uses eslint-config-next 15.5.0 for Next.js specific rules
- **Additional**: @eslint/eslintrc ^3 for configuration compatibility

## Development Workflow

### Package Management
- **Tool**: npm (with package-lock.json for consistent installs)
- **Node Version**: Compatible with Node.js 20 LTS

### Build System
- **Bundler**: Turbopack (Next.js native, faster than Webpack)
- **Enabled**: Both dev and build commands use --turbopack flag

